<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 04 at 2:46PM CDT until July 04 at 3:15PM CDT by NWS Milwaukee</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 315 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN LAFAYETTE...GREEN AND SOUTHWESTERN ROCK COUNTIES...
At 246 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Albany to Stockton, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Law enforcement reports trees down.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Brodhead, Monticello, South Wayne, Browntown, Juda, Avon and
Jordan Center.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
